<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">June 17, 2024</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-june-17-2024/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-238650 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/1927_04_02-dinner_edited_edited_edited-150x150.jpg" alt="dinner party" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://www.theparisreview.org/blog/2024/06/13/the-people-who-fight-at-dinner-parties/" class="external" target="_blank">Sarah Miller on the pleasures of fighting at dinner parties</a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/art-books-music/a61073695/nikole-hannah-jones-black-salon/" class="external" target="_blank"><i><span style="font-weight: 400">The 1619 Project</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400">, five years on</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://lareviewofbooks.org/article/fools-rush-in-on-kenneth-angers-scorpio-rising/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Revisiting Kenneth Anger’s </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">Scorpio Rising</span></i></a></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-june-17-2024/"><button>More News</button></a></li>
<li id="lithub_podcastplayer_widget-4" class="widget widget_lithub_podcastplayer_widget"><div class="lithub-radio-container" data-podcast="latest" style="display: none;"><div class="radio-header">	<div class="logo-container"><a href="/lithub-radio/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lithub-podcasts/img/litradio-sm.png"></a></div>	<h2><a href="/lithub-radio/"><em>Lit hub</em> Radio</a></h2>	<div class="name-container"><a href="/lithub-radio/">Podcasts, Audiobooks &#43; More</a></div></div><div class="player-container">	<div class="stream-name-container"><span class="now-playing">Now Playing:</span><span class="stream-name"></span></div></div><div class="stations-container">	<div class="all-stations"><a href="/lithub-radio/" class="all-stations-button">All Stations</a></div>	<div class="stations-slider">		<div class="stations-scroll">			<div class="station"><embed src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lithub-podcasts/img/show-fiction-non-fiction.svg" class="fiction-non-fiction" alt="fiction/non/fiction"><div class="station-button" data-key="fiction_non_fiction">&nbsp;</div></div>			<div class="station"><embed src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lithub-podcasts/img/show-literary-disco.svg" class="literary-disco" alt="Literary Disco"><div class="station-button" data-key="literary_disco">&nbsp;</div></div>			<div class="station"><embed src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lithub-podcasts/img/show-new-book-01.svg"class="new-books" alt="New Books Network"><div class="station-button" data-key="new_books_network">&nbsp;</div></div>			<div class="station"><embed src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lithub-podcasts/img/show-otherppl.svg" class="other-ppl" alt="Otherppl with Brad Listi"><div class="station-button" data-key="otherppl_with_brad_listi">&nbsp;</div></div>			<div class="station"><embed src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lithub-podcasts/img/show-reading-women.svg" class="reading-women" alt="Reading Women"><div class="station-button" data-key="reading_women">&nbsp;</div></div>			<div class="station"><embed src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lithub-podcasts/img/show-so-many-books.svg"class="so-many-books" alt="So Many Damned Books"><div class="station-button" data-key="so_many_damn_books">&nbsp;</div></div>			<div class="station"><embed src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lithub-podcasts/img/show-fiction-non-fiction.svg" class="fiction-non-fiction" alt="fiction/non/fiction"><div class="station-button" data-key="fiction_non_fiction">&nbsp;</div></div>		</div>		<div class="stations-arrow"><!-- <img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lithub-podcasts/img/arrow.png"> --></div>	</div></div></div></li>
